    "He graduated from Williams College <em>cum laude</em> in 1925, studying further at the Pennsylvania Academy of Fine Arts between 1925-1928.": [],
    "In 1930 he joined the Detroit Institute of Art in its education department.": [
        [
            3,
            7,
            [
                "1930,"
            ]
        ]
    ],
    "He married Constance Coleman the following year.": [],
    "Richardson was appointed assistant director of the Institute in 1933, effectively running the institution while its director, <a href=\"/valentinerw\">Wilhelm Rheinhold Otto Valentiner</a>, lived in his native Germany.": [],
    "He joined the <em>Art Quarterly</em> as its editor in 1938 (remaining until 1967).": [],
    "His first book, <em>The Way of Western Art</em>, appeared in 1939.": [],
    "He followed this by <em>American Romantic Painting</em> in 1944.": [],
    "In 1945 Richardson succeeded Valentiner as director.": [
        [
